      <hedline>
        <hl1>Less Is Still More</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Peter Stamelman letter agrees with David Thomson's June 11 article praising filmmaker Robert Altman (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>As David Thomson properly points out [''Robert Altman's Decade of Astonishments,'' June 11], lesser Altman is still 100 times more interesting and rewarding than all the idiotic, insipid blockbusters the 80's and 90's have given us. And Mr. Thomson is also correct when he says that Altman, much like Bunuel and, in another medium, Yeats, still has it in him to delight and surprise us. Don't write him off yet.</p>
        <p>PETER STAMELMAN  Manhattan</p>
      </block>
